title: Banks get pulled into line by the Government, but will customers wear the cost?
text: Credit card surcharges, superannuation, and financial advice rules may get Government attention after the financial systems inquiry's recommendations, but could consumers lose any gains thanks to banks passing the costs of tighter regulation? ...
